article.headline: Princeton 73, Virginia Military 68
article.story: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Luke Owings scored 14 points including the first four in a 12-2 run to close the half to lead Princeton to a 73-68 victory over VMI in a consolation game Saturday of the BCA Classic at Ohio State's Value City Arena. Justin Conway led the Tigers (1-1) with 15 points, with Kyle Koncz adding 13. Chavis Holmes came off the bench to score 29 points for VMI (0-2), with Reggie Williams adding 11 and Matt Murrer 10. VMI led 22-21 late in the first half before Owings hit two layups to give Princeton the lead for good. The Tigers built the advantage to 33-24 at halftime and then Owings and Koncz hit 3-pointers to start the second half to push the lead to 15. Holmes' 3-pointer with 1:11 left cut the margin to 64-62, but Princeton's Lincoln Gunn countered with a 3-pointer and Conway made a layup to preserve the win. The Tigers will play Alabama A&M for fifth place in the tournament on Sunday. VMI meets South Dakota State for seventh place.
